Preheat your #oven{} to 220°. Chop the @potato{1}(chopped into 2cm cubes) (no need to
peel). Pop on a #baking tray{} and drizzle over a little @oil{}. Season with
@salt{} and @black pepper{}. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden
and crispy, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Halve, then remove the core from the @red pepper{1}(halved and chopped into 2cm
pieces) and chop into 2cm pieces. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion
shallot{1}(peeled and thinly sliced into half moons). Roughly chop the
@coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Peel and grate the
@garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain the
@sweetcorn{1}(drained in a sieve) in a #sieve{} and press with the back of a
#spoon{} to get all of the water out.

Put a #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil). Add half the sweetcorn and cook
until browned, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir once only. Transfer to a #bowl{} and
repeat with the remaining sweetcorn. When done, add a splash of oil to the
(now empty) pan and lower the heat to medium. Add the red pepper and shallot
and fry until softened, ~{5%minutes}. Add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}
more. Return the sweetcorn to the pan and remove from the heat.

Pop another frying pan on high heat. While it gets hot, rub the
@rump bistro steak{2}(seasoned with salt and pepper) with oil and season with
@salt{} and @black pepper{}. Once the pan is very hot, lay in the steaks and
cook for ~{2 1/2%minutes} on each side, then remove to a #board{}, cover with
#foil{} and rest.

> We like our steak medium-rare but if you like yours medium, give them ~{2%minutes} more on each side.

Lower the heat to medium. Add the @water{100%ml}, @chicken stock pot{1/2} and
half the @chipotle paste{1}(spicy!). Stir to dissolve the stock pot and
simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the @creme fraiche{1}, bring to
the boil and then remove from the heat. Taste and add more chipotle paste if
you like it hot!

Reheat the sweetcorn over medium heat. When the potato is crispy, add to the
pan and stir through the coriander. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} to
taste. This is your hash! Slice the steak as thinly as possible.

> Add any resting juices from the steak into your creamy sauce for maximum flavour!

Share the hash between your plates, top with the steak and then drizzle over
the chipotle sauce. Enjoy!